The paper deals with a game-theoretic analysis of a mechanism for allocating divisible resources, which suggests that it could belong to the cs.GT (Game Theory) sub-category. The mechanism involves users submitting bids, which implies that it could also belong to the cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) sub-category. The paper also involves optimization and lower bounds, which could place it in the cs.IT (Information Theory) and cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) sub-categories. Finally, the paper deals with the efficiency of equilibria, which suggests that it could belong to the cs.LG (Machine Learning) sub-category.
